BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:5NjJkko_dnLo_IV12EWjt
SUMMARY:GSBA Open House
DTSTAMP:20260214T003547Z
DTSTART:20260224T000000Z
DESCRIPTION:Description GSBA Open House Happy Hour Join us for an open-hous
	e style happy hour and spend some time connecting with the GSBA community.
	 This casual networking event is designed for new members and longtime mem
	bers alike who want to build relationships\, reconnect with GSBA\, and lea
	rn more about the people and programs behind our work. Enjoy light snacks\
	, drinks \\(including non-alcoholic options\\)\, and easy conversation whi
	le meeting fellow members and the GSBA team. Event Details Date: Monday\, 
	February 23 Time: 4:00-5:30 PM Notes: Snacks and drinks will be provided\,
	 with non-alcoholic options available. What to Expect A Welcoming Space to
	 Connect Spend time in an open\, relaxed setting designed to make it easy 
	to meet people and start conversations. Member-to-Member Networking Connec
	t with other GSBA members-especially those who are new or looking to deepe
	n their involvement. Meet the GSBA Team Our staff will be on hand to intro
	duce themselves\, answer questions\, and share how our programs support me
	mbers throughout the year. Member Benefits Overview Learn more about GSBA 
	benefits\, events\, and opportunities-and how to make the most of your mem
	bership. Open Conversation Bring your ideas\, questions\, and updates. Thi
	s is an informal space to connect\, listen\, and share.
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/gsba-open-house/17865903/
	2026-02-23T00
LOCATION:GSBA\, 400 E Pine St Ste 322\, Seattle\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H30M
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:d9oX3hxDRLz1gsRZenm79
SUMMARY:Veteran Service Provider Networking Hour
DTSTAMP:20260214T003547Z
DTSTART:20260224T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Description Hello Fellow Providers\, Thank you to those who att
	ended last month&'s networking coffee hour event at MVCC. I love seeing th
	e depth of conversation and community we get in an in person setting. I've
	 been playing around with the name and date of this event\, but we decided
	 it might be more beneficial to plan these networking events around our Mi
	nority Veterans Training Program. So please feel free to come for the coff
	ee and networking and stay for a training on "Understanding and Honoring t
	he Black Military Experience. Which will begin at 1130. Coffee\, soft drin
	ks\, and snacks will be provided. What to expect: - Informal\, come-as-you
	-are networking - Connection with fellow Veteran service providers If you'
	re interested in attending\, hosting in the future\, or learning more\, I'
	d love to connect. Please feel free to share this invitation with colleagu
	es who may also benefit. Parking can be a little tight at the community ce
	nter at times. If the lot directly in front of the building is full\, ther
	e is an overflow lot just behind it. When you enter the building\, we are 
	located on the second floor all the way down past the elevators. The build
	ing is ADA accessible through the side entrance. I hope to see you there. 
	Please invite your colleagues.
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/veteran-service-provider-
	networking-hour/18089666/2026-02-24T00
LOCATION:Minority Vets Community Center\, 16040 Christensen Road\, Suite 21
	2\, Tukwila\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H30M
END:VEVENT
