BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:dY0wqdsCM-CJjmdd9GHfE
SUMMARY:Family Business Exchange | Lunch: Generational Transitions
DTSTAMP:20260214T003547Z
DTSTART:20260226T193000Z
DESCRIPTION:The Family Business Exchange and Clark Nuber host a hands-on wo
	rkshop focused on how family businesses can successfully transition leader
	ship across generations while preserving core values.  As a follow-up to t
	he January FBX evening seminar\, this workshop will provide family busines
	s owners with strategies for balancing tradition with innovation to ensure
	 long-term success.  Lunch and a complimentary parking pass will be provid
	ed.\n\n \n\nAbout the Family Business Exchange\n\nSeattle University’s Fam
	ily Business Exchange \\(FBX\\) is a community of Pacific Northwest family
	 business owners who gather to engage in education\, networking\, and prof
	essional development tailored specifically to their needs.\n\nFBX provides
	 opportunities for families to address their unique challenges through rel
	evant programming. It serves as a forum for information exchange with the 
	goal of helping each member thrive through future generations. Areas of be
	st practice that we cover include family business succession planning\, go
	vernance\, leadership development and growth\, among others.\n\n \n\nAbout
	 Clark Nuber\n\nFor over 70 years\, Clark Nuber has provided sophisticated
	 accounting and consulting services to clients across the U.S. and through
	out the world. To connect with Clark Nuber\, contact Julie Eisenhauer.\n\n
	 \n\nThis event is open to FBX members and prospective members.
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/family-business-exchange-
	lunch-generational-transitions/17717209/2026-02-26T00
LOCATION:Casey Building\, 530\, Seattle\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H30M
END:VEVENT
